icy and Operations Director with the rank of [[Brigadier General]].<ref>[http://www.newera.com.na/article.php?db=oldarchive&articleid=13677 Shalli New NDF Chief] New Era, 23 October 2006</ref>He was then promoted to Major General and appointed NDF Chief of Staff in 1995 replacing  Major General Charles Namholo. Between 2000 and 2005 he was the [[Namibian Army|Army Commander]] with the rank of Major General. In he was then appointed in 2005 to 2006 as the Namibian High Commissioner to Zambia. In 2006 he was promoted to Lieutenant General and appointed to Chief of Defence Force, [[Namibian Defence Force]]. In 2009, Shalli was suspended from the NDF due to allegations of fraud. He allegedly had large amounts of money given to him by a company working in Namibia from the [[People's Republic of China]] from which the NDF bought equipment. Major General [[Peter Nambundunga]] was appointed to Act in position.<ref name=Suspended/> Prior to his suspension, Shalli earned three medals for his service, the Order of Eagle 2nd Class, the [[Omugulugwombashe Medal]], and the Namibia Cross for Bravery in Silver. Despite the allegations, Shalli retired with full military privileges in January 2011.<ref name=Retire/>\n\n===Decorations===\n* [[File:NDF commendation ribbon.png|x18px]] NDF Commendation Medal\n* [[File:Namibian Cross for Bravery Ribbon (Gold).png|x18px]] Namibian Cross for bravery(Gold) Medal\n* [[File:Namibian Cross for Bravery Ribbon (Silver).png|x18px]] Namibian Cross for bravery(Silver) Medal\n\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef\n| before = [[Solomon Huwala]]\n}}\n{{s-ttl\n| title = [[Chief of the Defence Force (Namibia)|Chief of Defence Force]]\n| years = 2006{{snd}}24 January 2011\n}}\n{{s-aft\n| after = [[Epaphras Denga Ndaitwah]]\n\n}}{{s-bef\n| before = [[Solomon Huwala]]\n}}\n{{s-ttl\n| title = Commander [[Namibian Army]]\n| years = 2000{{snd}} 2005\n}}\n{{s-aft\n| after = [[Peter Nambundunga]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shalli, Martin}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:High Commissioners of Namibia to Zambia]]\n[[Category:People's Liberation Army of Namibia personnel]]\n[[Category:Namibian military personnel]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n\n\n{{Africa-diplomat-stub}}\n{{Namibia-mil-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "ViceAdmiral", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDecorations", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin_Shalli"}
